---
description: API documentation rules
globs: ["**/Startup.cs", "**/Program.cs", "**/Controllers/*.cs"]
---

- Use `Swashbuckle.AspNetCore` for Swagger generation.
- Annotate endpoints with `[ProducesResponseType]` and `[Consumes]`.
- Group endpoints by tag for clarity.
- Hide internal or admin endpoints from public docs.
- Use proper HTTP status codes for responses.
- Document request/response models with XML comments.
- Use OpenAPI 3.0 specifications.
- Implement proper API versioning.
- Use consistent naming conventions for endpoints.
- Document authentication and authorization requirements.
- Include examples in API documentation.
- Use proper content types (application/json, etc.).